The paper proposes a scheme for distributed learning tasks on wireless edge nodes, which involves optimization and communication aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to optimization, distributed learning, and deep learning. The paper also deals with communication and networking aspects, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The proposed scheme involves heterogeneous computing capacities, which could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), depending on the specific focus of the paper.
